Guidelines for Arapahoe Volleyball Triangular on 9.15.20

ARAPAHOE PANDEMIC RESPONSE COMMITTEE GUIDELINES HS JV & VARSITY VOLLEYBALL PUBLIC ATTENDANCE REQUIREMENTS UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE:

1. Doors will not open to fans until 4:15 pm to limit interaction between students and adults.
2. Fans are to self-monitor temperature prior to game and stay home if they have a fever of over 100.4°F or has COVID-19 symptoms that cannot be attributed to another condition.
3. Fans will enter the south and west doors.
4. Facemasks are required while in the building.
5. Every other row of seating will be taped off for social distancing purposes.
6. The court is off limit to fans.
7. Fans please exit the building when games are finished so there is no congregating in the commons area.
8. The south restrooms will be for use by the home team the north and gym restrooms will be for the visiting team.
9. Teams will not switch benches and will not shake hands before or after games.
10. All games will be available on https://striv.tv/channel/arapahoe/ for those who do not wish to follow these guidelines

post_text: We have been notified through USDA and the Nebraska Department of Education Nutrition Services that we are eligible to offer all our PreK-12 students’ a free breakfast and free lunch. For lunches, the meal and one milk will be free, however, if a student has an additional milk they will be charged for the milk. At the middle school and high school students choosing to eat via the a-la-carte will still be charged. This program will be effective starting Monday, September 14th and will be available each day that school is in session to possibly the end of the first semester (December 18).

Cozad FFA
September 4 at 8:54 PM ·

Our FFA Chapter was recently recognized by Pioneer Hi-Bred Int'l (Corteva Agriscience) with a grant to further support the start-up and ongoing sustainability and success of our FFA chapter. Pioneer makes contributions to community-based organizations on behalf of the company and employees. Consideration for outreach grants is given to communities where Pioneer sales representatives, farmer dealers, employees and customers live and work and that support quality-of-life initiatives to create an improved, sustainable lifestyle for people worldwide.

We would like to thank Charlie Shoemaker and Scott Bartels for helping our chapter with this grant!

post_text:
Announcement Update--Effective September 1st, 2020 --For pre-K-12 teachers, para-educators and other certificated and non-certificated staff employed by schools who have had close contact with a person whom has tested positive, or has had close contact with a person whom has a test pending and is symptomatic, or has had close contact with a person with one or more of the Covid symptoms. Educational Workers may meet the following Conditions while performing their duties of their employment with schools In Lieu of Quarantine:

1. appropriately wear a face covering or mask for 14 days following exposure, AND
2. practice social distancing, AND
3. self-monitor twice daily for fever and other symptoms listed above for fourteen days and have no symptom development

This means if a school employee is told to quarantine they may come to work following the above guidelines. If the staff member is a teacher or para, students will be asked to wear masks in that classroom.

EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITY
Cozad Community Schools is seeking applicants for a full-time Special Education Paraprofessional at the Elementary School. This is a 9-month, 35 hour per week position. Benefits include single health, dental and vision insurance. Application forms are available at the District Office, 1910 Meridian Ave, or are available on the school’s website (www.cozadschools.net). Please call 308-784-2745 for additional information. Position subject to veteran’s preference. EOE.

post_text:
Throughout the school year, Alyssa Kolbo, Katie Wilson, and Madison Rowley took Fashion Design class through the FCS department at our high school. They each designed and created an outfit and applied for Omaha Fashion Week. Where they had the chance to model their first outfits and later went on to create their own clothing line.

Madi and Katie both used their deigns to compete in STAR. Madi competed in Fashion Construction earning 1st at Districts and 4th at State. Katie competed in Fashion Design earning 1st at Districts, 2nd at State, and 2nd at Nationals!!!

So proud of each of these young ladies for their accomplishments!!!
#CHS #NebraskaFCCLA
text:
Throughout the school year, Alyssa Kolbo, Katie Wilson, and Madison Rowley took Fashion Design class through the FCS department at our high school. They each designed and created an outfit and applied for Omaha Fashion Week. Where they had the chance to model their first outfits and later went on to create their own clothing line.

Madi and Katie both used their deigns to compete in STAR. Madi competed in Fashion Construction earning 1st at Districts and 4th at State. Katie competed in Fashion Design earning 1st at Districts, 2nd at State, and 2nd at Nationals!!!

So proud of each of these young ladies for their accomplishments!!!
#CHS #NebraskaFCCLA

At Natural Escapes, we support teachers and are so very appreciative of all you do for our kids and community. So if you are employed by Cozad Community Schools as faculty, staff, or administration (so EVERYONE), please stop by our 708 Maple Street location and pick up your one FREE annual ($6.99 value or less).

Thank you for all you do! Please help us share and get the word out!

(When checking out, simply tell us you are claiming your free annual as you are employed by CCS. One per CCS employee based upon an honor system.)

post_text:
Reminder: Starting Wednesday, May 6th, Cozad Schools will change it’s meal delivery schedule.

We will provide meal pick up on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays.

On Mondays, we will provide Breakfast and Lunch for Monday and Tuesday. Wednesday we will provide Breakfast and Lunch for Wednesday and Thursday. Friday we will provide Breakfast and Lunch for Friday, Saturday and Sunday.

This will save parents and children from having to come to our 6 meal sites every day. We hope you see this as a convenience.

This new meal schedule will begin on Wednesday, May 6th with 2 days of meals. We will serve our normal schedule until that point.

Menus are available through the Cozad app or cozadschools.nutrislice.com.

Reminder: Starting Wednesday, May 6th, Cozad Schools will change it’s meal delivery schedule.

We will provide meal pick up on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays.

On Mondays, we will provide Breakfast and Lunch for Monday and Tuesday. Wednesday we will provide Breakfast and Lunch for Wednesday and Thursday. Friday we will provide Breakfast and Lunch for Friday, Saturday and Sunday.

This will save parents and children from having to come to our 6 meal sites every day. We hope you see this as a convenience.

This new meal schedule will begin on Wednesday, May 6th with 2 days of meals. We will serve our normal schedule until that point.

Menus are available through the Cozad app or cozadschools.nutrislice.com.

COZADSCHOOLS.NUTRISLICE.COM
Nutrislice Menus | Cozad Community Schools

Information on meal program in Spanish:

Aquí está la información sobre el nuevo horario de comidas:

A partir del miércoles 6 de mayo, las Escuelas de Cozad cambiarán su horario de entrega de comidas.

Brindáremos servicio de recogida de comida los lunes, miércoles y viernes.

Los lunes, proporcionaremos desayuno y almuerzo para lunes y martes. El miércoles proporcionaremos desayuno y almuerzo los miércoles y jueves. Viernes proporcionaremos desayuno y almuerzo para viernes, sábado y domingo.

Esto evitará que padres e hijos tengan que venir a nuestros 6 sitios de comidas todos los días. Esperamos que vea esto como una conveniencia.

Este nuevo horario de comidas comenzará el miércoles 6 de mayo con 2 días de comidas. Serviremos nuestro horario normal hasta ese punto

Cozad Community Schools is pleased to announce that Kaylei Becker has been named the new Girls Golf Coach at Cozad High School. Coach Becker is a 2017
Cozad graduate and decorated golfer while in high school. During her high school playing career, she was a 4-time letter winner, 3-time state qualifier and two year
state medalist (2nd place-2015, 4th place-2016). After high school, she played college golf at UNK. She has also assisted in the summer golf programs in Cozad.

post_text: Cozad Community Schools is pleased to announce that Darrel Francescato has been named the new Head Volleyball Coach at Cozad High School. Coach Francescato was previously the head volleyball coach at Cozad from 2013-2016 and an assistant coach from 2008-2014. He has been involved with coaching club volleyball at various levels for twenty years along with officiating the sport.

post_text:
Cozad Community Schools is pleased to announce that Nick Broz has been named the new Head Boys Basketball Coach at Cozad High School. Coach Broz comes to Cozad after spending ten years as a Physical Education teacher, Strength/Conditioning teacher and Head Basketball coach at Bridgeport High School. Prior to his years at Bridgeport, Coach Broz was an assistant coach at Hastings College and McCook Community College. His playing experience in college includes time at Hastings College and McCook Community College where he was team captain for both teams.
Coach Broz was honored as the Scottsbluff Star-Herald All-Region Coach of the year in 2019 and his team qualified for the state tournament in 2015 and 2019. His
team also won conference championships in the WTC (2014, 2015, 2019, 2020) and SPVA (2016, 2019) conferences.

shared_text:
Beatriz Reyna News 2
April 6 at 5:29 AM ·

Teachers at Cozad Community Schools are going bananas without their students 🍌🍌

So much, that a group of teachers took it upon themselves to organize a parade of their own!

On Wednesday, about 30 teachers, including para-professionals, drove through their students’ neighborhoods eager to see their smiles and say “hello.”

Some students made signs to hold with messages such as “Hugs.”

Families were instructed to practice social distancing by standing outside their homes or parking and staying in their cars along the route.

Teachers say not only did they have “tears of joy,” but it was also difficult to stay away and not “hug each and every single person!”

School officials say the parade helped promote the school’s Social Distancing and Staying Safe at Home Rules.

Photo Courtesy: Karen Berreckman

https://www.knopnews2.com/content/news/Cozad-teachers-on-parade-569398071.html

post_text:
Message from Cozad Community Schools Superintendent Ron Wymore: This is to let you know that the school buildings will be closed until at least May 31st. This is a part of a new Directed Health Measure issued by Governor Ricketts. Graduation is postponed and will be rescheduled at a later date in accordance with regulations from the Two Rivers Health. NSAA has cancelled all activity practices and competitions including district and state competitions for the remainder of the school year.

Cozad Community Schools will continue with our on-line education for all students until the end of the school year. Your child needs to make sure to do the on-line activities and assignments for the rest of the year. Not doing the assignments could jeopardize their credits for the second semester classes.

Stay healthy and practice social distancing.

If you are interested in being a chapter officer for the 2020-2021 school year, please fill out this application by Wednesday April 8th at 12:00pm.

We will be conducting LIVE interviews, via Zoom on Wednesday April 15th from 4:00-8:00pm. Please be available with access to a computer and internet. If this will not work, please contact Ms. Crowe ASAP.

Thanks!
